{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":822,"text":"So over the long course of human history,"},{"time":4257,"text":"the infectious disease that's killed more humans"},{"time":6749,"text":"than any other is malaria."},{"time":9235,"text":"It's carried in the bites of infected mosquitos,"},{"time":12096,"text":"and it's probably our oldest scourge."},{"time":14305,"text":"We may have had malaria since we evolved from the apes."},{"time":18192,"text":"And to this day, malaria takes a huge toll on our species."},{"time":21794,"text":"We've got 300 million cases a year"},{"time":24245,"text":"and over half a million deaths."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27237,"text":"Now this really makes no sense."},{"time":30202,"text":"We've known how to cure malaria"},{"time":32854,"text":"since the 1600s."},{"time":34494,"text":"That's when Jesuit missionaries in Peru"},{"time":36791,"text":"discovered the bark of the cinchona tree,"},{"time":39693,"text":"and inside that bark was quinine,"},{"time":41566,"text":"still an effective cure for malaria to this day."},{"time":44904,"text":"So we've known how to cure malaria for centuries."},{"time":47805,"text":"We've known how to prevent malaria since 1897."},{"time":50989,"text":"That's when the British army surgeon Ronald Ross"},{"time":53262,"text":"discovered that it was mosquitos that carried malaria,"},{"time":56620,"text":"not bad air or miasmas, as was previously thought."},{"time":60812,"text":"So malaria should be a relatively simple disease to solve,"},{"time":66095,"text":"and yet to this day, hundreds of thousands of people"},{"time":70025,"text":"are going to die from the bite of a mosquito."},{"time":73500,"text":"Why is that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":74745,"text":"This is a question that's"},{"time":76275,"text":"personally intrigued me for a long time."},{"time":78430,"text":"I grew up as the daughter of Indian immigrants"},{"time":81189,"text":"visiting my cousins in India every summer,"},{"time":83448,"text":"and because I had no immunity to the local malarias,"},{"time":86636,"text":"I was made to sleep under this hot, sweaty mosquito net every night"},{"time":90870,"text":"while my cousins, they were allowed to sleep"},{"time":92561,"text":"out on the terrace and have"},{"time":93790,"text":"this nice, cool night breeze wafting over them."},{"time":96552,"text":"And I really hated the mosquitos for that."},{"time":100076,"text":"But at the same time, I come from a Jain family,"},{"time":103444,"text":"and Jainism is a religion that espouses"},{"time":105758,"text":"a very extreme form of nonviolence."},{"time":108896,"text":"So Jains are not supposed to eat meat."},{"time":112224,"text":"We're not supposed to walk on grass,"},{"time":114081,"text":"because you could, you know,"},{"time":115342,"text":"inadvertently kill some insects when you walk on grass."},{"time":117242,"text":"We're certainly not supposed to swat mosquitos."},{"time":120019,"text":"So the fearsome power of this little insect"},{"time":123735,"text":"was apparent to me from a very young age,"},{"time":125714,"text":"and it's one reason why I spent five years as a journalist"},{"time":128985,"text":"trying to understand, why has malaria"},{"time":131673,"text":"been such a horrible scourge for all of us for so very long?"},{"time":136213,"text":"And I think there's three main reasons why."},{"time":138870,"text":"Those three reasons add up to the fourth reason,"},{"time":141338,"text":"which is probably the biggest reason of all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144149,"text":"The first reason is certainly scientific."},{"time":147110,"text":"This little parasite that causes malaria,"},{"time":149425,"text":"it's probably one of the most complex"},{"time":151352,"text":"and wily pathogens known to humankind."},{"time":153943,"text":"It lives half its life inside the cold-blooded mosquito"},{"time":157283,"text":"and half its life inside the warm-blooded human."},{"time":161685,"text":"These two environments are totally different,"},{"time":164683,"text":"but not only that, they're both utterly hostile."},{"time":167699,"text":"So the insect is continually trying to fight off the parasite,"},{"time":171706,"text":"and so is the human body continually trying to fight it off."},{"time":174667,"text":"This little creature survives under siege like that,"},{"time":178417,"text":"but not only does it survive, it has thrived."},{"time":181492,"text":"It has spread. It has more ways to evade attack than we know."},{"time":185814,"text":"It's a shape-shifter, for one thing."},{"time":187928,"text":"Just as a caterpillar turns into a butterfly,"},{"time":191087,"text":"the malaria parasite transforms itself like that"},{"time":193726,"text":"seven times in its life cycle."},{"time":196949,"text":"And each of those life stages not only looks totally different from each other,"},{"time":201206,"text":"they have totally different physiology."},{"time":204270,"text":"So say you came up with some great drug"},{"time":206262,"text":"that worked against one stage of the parasite's life cycle."},{"time":209202,"text":"It might do nothing at all to any of the other stages."},{"time":212667,"text":"It can hide in our bodies, undetected,"},{"time":215530,"text":"unbeknownst to us, for days, for weeks,"},{"time":217894,"text":"for months, for years, in some cases even decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221693,"text":"So the parasite is a very big scientific challenge to tackle,"},{"time":226077,"text":"but so is the mosquito that carries the parasite."},{"time":229282,"text":"Only about 12 species of mosquitos"},{"time":231580,"text":"carry most of the world's malaria,"},{"time":233514,"text":"and we know quite a bit about the kinds of"},{"time":235990,"text":"watery habitats that they specialize in."},{"time":238915,"text":"So you might think, then, well, why don't we just"},{"time":241197,"text":"avoid the places where the killer mosquitos live? Right?"},{"time":244353,"text":"We could avoid the places where the killer grizzly bears live"},{"time":246631,"text":"and we avoid the places where the killer crocodiles live."},{"time":249390,"text":"But say you live in the tropics"},{"time":252620,"text":"and you walk outside your hut one day"},{"time":255893,"text":"and you leave some footprints in the soft dirt"},{"time":257915,"text":"around your home."},{"time":259838,"text":"Or say your cow does, or say your pig does,"},{"time":263068,"text":"and then, say, it rains,"},{"time":265202,"text":"and that footprint fills up with a little bit of water."},{"time":267570,"text":"That's it. You've created the perfect"},{"time":269651,"text":"malarial mosquito habitat that's right outside your door."},{"time":273229,"text":"So it's not easy for us to extricate ourselves from these insects."},{"time":276091,"text":"We kind of create places that they love to live"},{"time":278725,"text":"just by living our own lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280724,"text":"So there's a huge scientific challenge,"},{"time":282103,"text":"but there's a huge economic challenge too."},{"time":284310,"text":"Malaria occurs in some of the poorest"},{"time":286245,"text":"and most remote places on Earth,"},{"time":288184,"text":"and there's a reason for that."},{"time":290029,"text":"If you're poor, you're more likely to get malaria."},{"time":292729,"text":"If you're poor, you're more likely to live"},{"time":294882,"text":"in rudimentary housing on marginal land that's poorly drained."},{"time":298951,"text":"These are places where mosquitos breed."},{"time":301540,"text":"You're less likely to have door screens or window screens."},{"time":305140,"text":"You're less likely to have electricity"},{"time":307043,"text":"and all the indoor activities that electricity makes possible,"},{"time":310049,"text":"so you're outside more."},{"time":311282,"text":"You're getting bitten by mosquitos more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313614,"text":"So poverty causes malaria,"},{"time":315239,"text":"but what we also know now is that malaria itself"},{"time":318272,"text":"causes poverty."},{"time":319919,"text":"For one thing, it strikes hardest during harvest season,"},{"time":322570,"text":"so exactly when farmers need to be out in the fields"},{"time":325326,"text":"collecting their crops, they're home sick with a fever."},{"time":329235,"text":"But it also predisposes people to death"},{"time":332096,"text":"from all other causes."},{"time":333881,"text":"So this has happened historically."},{"time":335241,"text":"We've been able to take malaria out of a society."},{"time":338623,"text":"Everything else stays the same,"},{"time":340080,"text":"so we still have bad food, bad water, bad sanitation,"},{"time":342755,"text":"all the things that make people sick."},{"time":344516,"text":"But just if you take malaria out,"},{"time":346660,"text":"deaths from everything else go down."},{"time":350472,"text":"And the economist Jeff Sachs has actually quantified"},{"time":353183,"text":"what this means for a society."},{"time":355368,"text":"What it means is, if you have malaria in your society,"},{"time":358122,"text":"your economic growth is depressed"},{"time":360583,"text":"by 1.3 percent every year,"},{"time":364553,"text":"year after year after year, just this one disease alone."},{"time":368352,"text":"So this poses a huge economic challenge,"},{"time":370916,"text":"because say you do come up with your great drug"},{"time":373100,"text":"or your great vaccine -- how do you deliver it"},{"time":375310,"text":"in a place where there's no roads,"},{"time":377880,"text":"there's no infrastructure,"},{"time":379073,"text":"there's no electricity for refrigeration to keep things cold,"},{"time":382407,"text":"there's no clinics, there's no clinicians"},{"time":385127,"text":"to deliver these things where they're needed?"},{"time":387661,"text":"So there's a huge economic challenge in taming malaria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391664,"text":"But along with the scientific challenge and the economic challenge,"},{"time":394720,"text":"there's also a cultural challenge,"},{"time":396532,"text":"and this is probably the part about malaria"},{"time":399917,"text":"that people don't like to talk about."},{"time":402218,"text":"And it's the paradox that the people"},{"time":404929,"text":"who have the most malaria in the world"},{"time":406737,"text":"tend to care about it the least."},{"time":409317,"text":"This has been the finding of medical anthropologists again and again."},{"time":412729,"text":"They ask people in malarious parts of the world,"},{"time":415496,"text":"\"What do you think about malaria?\""},{"time":417552,"text":"And they don't say, \"It's a killer disease. We're scared of it.\""},{"time":421461,"text":"They say, \"Malaria is a normal problem of life.\""},{"time":426799,"text":"And that was certainly my personal experience."},{"time":428565,"text":"When I told my relatives in India"},{"time":430584,"text":"that I was writing a book about malaria,"},{"time":432068,"text":"they kind of looked at me like"},{"time":434035,"text":"I told them I was writing a book about warts or something."},{"time":436736,"text":"Like, why would you write about something so boring,"},{"time":439783,"text":"so ordinary? You know?"},{"time":441449,"text":"And it's simple risk perception, really."},{"time":444177,"text":"A child in Malawi, for example,"},{"time":446612,"text":"she might have 12 episodes of malaria before the age of two,"},{"time":451424,"text":"but if she survives,"},{"time":453477,"text":"she'll continue to get malaria throughout her life,"},{"time":456091,"text":"but she's much less likely to die of it."},{"time":458814,"text":"And so in her lived experience,"},{"time":460766,"text":"malaria is something that comes and goes."},{"time":464097,"text":"And that's actually true for most of the world's malaria."},{"time":466127,"text":"Most of the world's malaria comes and goes on its own."},{"time":469704,"text":"It's just, there's so much malaria"},{"time":472828,"text":"that this tiny fraction of cases that end in death"},{"time":476599,"text":"add up to this big, huge number."},{"time":479560,"text":"So I think people in malarious parts of the world"},{"time":481553,"text":"must think of malaria the way"},{"time":483075,"text":"those of us who live in the temperate world"},{"time":484734,"text":"think of cold and flu. Right?"},{"time":486985,"text":"Cold and flu have a huge burden on our societies"},{"time":490391,"text":"and on our own lives,"},{"time":492072,"text":"but we don't really even take"},{"time":493336,"text":"the most rudimentary precautions against it because"},{"time":495878,"text":"we consider it normal to get cold and flu"},{"time":498599,"text":"during cold and flu season."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500836,"text":"And so this poses a huge cultural challenge in taming malaria,"},{"time":505248,"text":"because if people think it's normal to have malaria,"},{"time":509022,"text":"then how do you get them to run to the doctor"},{"time":512480,"text":"to get diagnosed, to pick up their prescription,"},{"time":515626,"text":"to get it filled, to take the drugs,"},{"time":517148,"text":"to put on the repellents, to tuck in the bed nets?"},{"time":520627,"text":"This is a huge cultural challenge in taming this disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525294,"text":"So take all that together."},{"time":526796,"text":"We've got a disease. It's scientifically complicated,"},{"time":531248,"text":"it's economically challenging to deal with,"},{"time":533676,"text":"and it's one for which the people who stand"},{"time":535321,"text":"to benefit the most care about it the least."},{"time":537625,"text":"And that adds up to the biggest problem of all,"},{"time":539713,"text":"which, of course, is the political problem."},{"time":542662,"text":"How do you get a political leader to do anything"},{"time":545520,"text":"about a problem like this?"},{"time":547581,"text":"And the answer is, historically, you don't."},{"time":552206,"text":"Most malarious societies throughout history"},{"time":554339,"text":"have simply lived with the disease."},{"time":556455,"text":"So the main attacks on malaria have come"},{"time":558458,"text":"from outside of malarious societies,"},{"time":561082,"text":"from people who aren't constrained"},{"time":562876,"text":"by these rather paralyzing politics."},{"time":565855,"text":"But this, I think, introduces a whole host of other kinds of difficulties."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569150,"text":"The first concerted attack against malaria"},{"time":571570,"text":"started in the 1950s."},{"time":573316,"text":"It was the brainchild of the U.S. State Department."},{"time":576406,"text":"And this effort well understood the economic challenge."},{"time":579443,"text":"They knew they had to focus on cheap, easy-to-use tools,"},{"time":582924,"text":"and they focused on DDT."},{"time":584699,"text":"They understood the cultural challenge."},{"time":586138,"text":"In fact, their rather patronizing view was that"},{"time":589143,"text":"people at risk of malaria shouldn't be asked to do anything at all."},{"time":592046,"text":"Everything should be done to them and for them."},{"time":595768,"text":"But they greatly underestimated the scientific challenge."},{"time":598888,"text":"They had so much faith in their tools"},{"time":601215,"text":"that they stopped doing malaria research."},{"time":604206,"text":"And so when those tools started to fail,"},{"time":606674,"text":"and public opinion started to turn against those tools,"},{"time":609374,"text":"they had no scientific expertise to figure out what to do."},{"time":613568,"text":"The whole campaign crashed, malaria resurged back,"},{"time":617019,"text":"but now it was even worse than before"},{"time":618833,"text":"because it was corralled into the hardest-to-reach places"},{"time":621594,"text":"in the most difficult-to-control forms."},{"time":624780,"text":"One WHO official at the time actually called that whole campaign"},{"time":628079,"text":"\"one of the greatest mistakes ever made in public health.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":633136,"text":"The latest effort to tame malaria started in the late 1990s."},{"time":635643,"text":"It's similarly directed and financed primarily"},{"time":639355,"text":"from outside of malarious societies."},{"time":641503,"text":"Now this effort well understands the scientific challenge."},{"time":644007,"text":"They are doing tons of malaria research."},{"time":646228,"text":"And they understand the economic challenge too."},{"time":648681,"text":"They're focusing on very cheap, very easy-to-use tools."},{"time":652241,"text":"But now, I think, the dilemma is the cultural challenge."},{"time":656133,"text":"The centerpiece of the current effort is the bed net."},{"time":659767,"text":"It's treated with insecticides."},{"time":661543,"text":"This thing has been distributed across the malarious world"},{"time":663913,"text":"by the millions."},{"time":665346,"text":"And when you think about the bed net,"},{"time":667578,"text":"it's sort of a surgical intervention."},{"time":670137,"text":"You know, it doesn't really have any value"},{"time":672283,"text":"to a family with malaria except that it helps prevent malaria."},{"time":675946,"text":"And yet we're asking people to use these nets every night."},{"time":679955,"text":"They have to sleep under them every night."},{"time":681232,"text":"That's the only way they are effective."},{"time":683269,"text":"And they have to do that"},{"time":684622,"text":"even if the net blocks the breeze,"},{"time":687708,"text":"even if they might have to get up in the middle of the night"},{"time":690853,"text":"and relieve themselves,"},{"time":692387,"text":"even if they might have to move all their furnishings"},{"time":694636,"text":"to put this thing up,"},{"time":696103,"text":"even if, you know, they might live in a round hut"},{"time":698956,"text":"in which it's difficult to string up a square net."},{"time":702693,"text":"Now that's no big deal if you're fighting a killer disease."},{"time":707631,"text":"I mean, these are minor inconveniences."},{"time":709962,"text":"But that's not how people with malaria think of malaria."},{"time":713801,"text":"So for them, the calculus must be quite different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718681,"text":"Imagine, for example, if a bunch of well-meaning Kenyans"},{"time":722599,"text":"came up to those of us in the temperate world and said,"},{"time":724680,"text":"\"You know, you people have a lot of cold and flu."},{"time":727502,"text":"We've designed this great, easy-to-use, cheap tool,"},{"time":730630,"text":"we're going to give it to you for free."},{"time":731700,"text":"It's called a face mask,"},{"time":733133,"text":"and all you need to do is"},{"time":737006,"text":"wear it every day during cold and flu season"},{"time":739416,"text":"when you go to school and when you go to work.\""},{"time":742185,"text":"Would we do that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":744115,"text":"And I wonder if that's how people"},{"time":746251,"text":"in the malarious world thought of those nets"},{"time":748317,"text":"when they first received them?"},{"time":750020,"text":"Indeed, we know from studies"},{"time":753418,"text":"that only 20 percent of the bed nets"},{"time":756096,"text":"that were first distributed were actually used."},{"time":759264,"text":"And even that's probably an overestimate,"},{"time":760975,"text":"because the same people who distributed the nets"},{"time":763397,"text":"went back and asked the recipients,"},{"time":764888,"text":"\"Oh, did you use that net I gave you?\""},{"time":767361,"text":"Which is like your Aunt Jane asking you,"},{"time":769973,"text":"\"Oh, did you use that vase I gave you for Christmas?\""},{"time":772934,"text":"So it's probably an overestimate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774800,"text":"But that's not an insurmountable problem."},{"time":778124,"text":"We can do more education,"},{"time":779954,"text":"we can try to convince these people to use the nets."},{"time":782629,"text":"And that's what happening now."},{"time":783904,"text":"We're throwing a lot more time and money"},{"time":785608,"text":"into workshops and trainings and musicals and plays"},{"time":790125,"text":"and school meetings,"},{"time":792538,"text":"all these things to convince people"},{"time":794833,"text":"to use the nets we gave you."},{"time":797317,"text":"And that might work."},{"time":799457,"text":"But it takes time. It takes money."},{"time":802135,"text":"It takes resources. It takes infrastructure."},{"time":804915,"text":"It takes all the things that that cheap,"},{"time":807597,"text":"easy-to-use bed net was not supposed to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810376,"text":"So it's difficult to attack malaria from inside malarious societies,"},{"time":813780,"text":"but it's equally tricky when we try to attack it"},{"time":816318,"text":"from outside of those societies."},{"time":819128,"text":"We end up imposing our own priorities"},{"time":820915,"text":"on the people of the malarious world."},{"time":822459,"text":"That's exactly what we did in the 1950s,"},{"time":825253,"text":"and that effort backfired."},{"time":827131,"text":"I would argue today,"},{"time":828762,"text":"when we are distributing tools that we've designed"},{"time":832992,"text":"and that don't necessarily make sense in people's lives,"},{"time":836745,"text":"we run the risk of making the same mistake again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840298,"text":"That's not to say that malaria is unconquerable,"},{"time":842106,"text":"because I think it is,"},{"time":843569,"text":"but what if we attacked this disease"},{"time":845777,"text":"according to the priorities of the people who lived with it?"},{"time":849320,"text":"Take the example of England and the United States."},{"time":851756,"text":"We had malaria in those countries for hundreds of years,"},{"time":854927,"text":"and we got rid of it completely,"},{"time":857085,"text":"not because we attacked malaria. We didn't."},{"time":860094,"text":"We attacked bad roads and bad houses"},{"time":864201,"text":"and bad drainage and lack of electricity and rural poverty."},{"time":869083,"text":"We attacked the malarious way of life,"},{"time":872400,"text":"and by doing that, we slowly built malaria out."},{"time":878120,"text":"Now attacking the malarious way of life,"},{"time":879758,"text":"this is something -- these are things people care about today."},{"time":883320,"text":"And attacking the malarious way of life,"},{"time":885707,"text":"it's not fast, it's not cheap, it's not easy,"},{"time":890466,"text":"but I think it's the only lasting way forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893534,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894827,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}